    <!-- NOTES FOR ONTOLOGY MAINTAINERS:

    1. NAMESPACE RESOLUTION:
       This catalog maps OWL owl:imports IRIs to local file paths.
       When Protégé or other RDF tools encounter an owl:imports statement,
       they consult this catalog to find the local file instead of fetching
       from the network.

    2. ADDING NEW IMPORTS:
       - Add <uri> entries for new ontology imports
       - Keep external standards in ext/standard-ontologies/
       - Keep domain-specific ontologies in ext/domain-ontologies/
       - Keep alignment files in ext/responsiblesteel/alignments/

    3. FILE ORGANIZATION:
       ext/
       ├── responsiblesteel/
       │   ├── comet-rs-core.ttl
       │   ├── comet-rs-properties.ttl
       │   ├── comet-rs-individuals.ttl
       │   ├── labels/
       │   │   ├── comet-rs-labels-en.ttl
       │   │   ├── comet-rs-labels-zh.ttl
       │   │   └── ... (more languages)
       │   └── alignments/
       │       ├── comet-pact-alignment.ttl
       │       ├── comet-cbam-alignment.ttl
       │       ├── comet-esrs-alignment.ttl
       │       └── comet-ghgprotocol-alignment.ttl
       ├── standard-ontologies/
       │   ├── skos-core.rdf
       │   ├── dcterms.rdf
       │   ├── owl.rdf
       │   ├── rdfs.rdf
       │   └── ... (other W3C standards)
       └── domain-ontologies/
           ├── ghgprotocol-scopes.ttl
           ├── pact-pathfinder-v3.ttl
           ├── cbam.ttl
           ├── esrs.ttl
           └── ... (other domain ontologies)

    4. PROTÉGÉ USAGE:
       - Open this catalog in Protégé: File > Preferences > Ontology IRI Mappings
       - Import via owl:imports in your root ontology file
       - Use the IRI from <uri name="..."> in owl:imports statements
       - Protégé will automatically resolve to local files

    5. VALIDATION:
       Run validation scripts from tools/scripts/:
       - python check-i18n-coverage.py --core ext/responsiblesteel/comet-rs-core.ttl
       - python detect-breaking-changes.py old.ttl new.ttl
       - python validate-sources.py --files ext/responsiblesteel/*.ttl

    6. UPDATING THIS CATALOG:
       - Add entries when new files are created
       - Keep URIs and file paths in sync
       - Test with `rdflib.Graph().parse()` in Python
       - Validate with Protégé's ontology validation tools
    -->

</catalog>
